        <div class="verdict">⭐ Rating: 4.1/5 — Best for service contractors prioritizing customer experience and scheduling efficiency</div>

        <p>Commusoft started in the UK serving HVAC, plumbing, electrical, and property maintenance contractors. It's grown into a comprehensive field service management platform with a particularly strong focus on the customer-facing side: booking portals, automated notifications, customer communication logs, and branded service reports. In North America, it competes directly with ServiceTitan, Jobber, and FieldEdge — with a strong case for contractors who prioritize the customer experience side of their business.</p>

        <p>The platform covers the full service contractor lifecycle: customer and property records, job scheduling and dispatch, field technician apps, invoicing, and customer portals. It's not a general contractor platform — it's purpose-built for service work (reactive and planned maintenance) rather than project-based construction.</p>

