        <h2>Who should use Commusoft?</h2>
        <p><strong>Good fit:</strong> Commercial HVAC, plumbing, electrical, and property maintenance contractors; companies with planned maintenance contract portfolios; service businesses that want to compete on customer experience quality; companies with 5–50+ technicians who need intelligent scheduling and dispatch.</p>
        <p><strong>Not ideal for:</strong> General contractors managing project-based construction; small one-or-two person service businesses (Jobber is simpler); companies heavily invested in ServiceTitan (switching costs are high); businesses needing deep US construction accounting integration.</p>

        <h2>The verdict</h2>
        <p>Commusoft is a genuinely strong platform for commercial service contractors who prioritize customer experience and operational efficiency. Its scheduled maintenance management, customer portal, and dispatch optimization tools are among the best in the field service management category. The UK origin means North American companies should verify integrations and support coverage before committing.</p>

        <p>For companies that primarily do reactive service work and planned maintenance — rather than project-based construction — Commusoft is worth a serious evaluation, particularly against ServiceTitan (if budget is a concern) or Jobber (if you've outgrown it).</p>

